Here's a simple HTML and JavaScript script that creates a form to input text and save it to local storage:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>Text Input Form</h2>

<form id="textForm">
  <label for="textInput">Enter text:</label><br>
  <input type="text" id="textInput" name="textInput"><br><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>

<script>
document.getElementById("textForm").addEventListener("submit", function(event) {
  event.preventDefault();
  const text = document.getElementById("textInput").value;
  localStorage.setItem("savedText", text);
  alert("Text saved to local storage!");
});
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

This script creates a form with a text input field and a submit button. When the form is submitted, the text is saved to local storage under the key "savedText". The alert function is used to notify the user that the text has been saved.
